Before discussing fingerprint detection times, it is useful to examine basic features of the fingerprint and noise patterns. The CanESM2 ALL fingerprints capture global-scale lower stratospheric cooling and tropospheric warming (
 
  SI Appendix, Fig. S4
 ). CESM1 ALL fingerprints (not shown) are very similar. The fingerprints are spatially dissimilar to smaller-scale, opposite-signed spatial features in the multimodel and single-model noise estimates (
 
  SI Appendix, Figs. S5 and S6
 ). This is favorable for signal identification (
 34).
